    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This is an add-on plugin specific for the <a href=\"https:\/\/total.wpexplorer.com\/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Total theme<\/a> (will not work with any other theme) which adds two new options inside the Theme Settings metabox while editing any taxonomy term via the WP admin so you can assign a template (WPBakery or Elementor) specific to the term archive or for the posts within that term.<\/p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload &#8216;term-based-dynamic-post-templates-for-total&#8217; to the &#8216;\/wp-content\/plugins\/&#8217; directory.<\/li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.<\/li>\n<li>You can now edit any taxonomy term and assign a template to it.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix Compatibility fix for Total 5.8.0+<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.1<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added ability to assign a custom template for the archive.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>First official release<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
